# LifeOS CLI Skill

Use the local `lifeos` CLI as the source of truth for LifeOS operations.

LifeOS core path:

```text
Input -> Facts -> Rules -> Passport -> Manual / Exchange
```

## Default Write Path

For "记一下", "记录", "remember this", "log this", completed work, decisions, learning, reflections, relationship events, project progress, or durable conversation context, prefer:

```bash
lifeos record --text "..."
```

Useful options:

```bash
lifeos record \
  --text "..." \
  --project LifeOS \
  --person "Name" \
  --tags "CLI,事实层" \
  --evidence "..."
```

`record` supports `--text`, stdin, `--input-json`, `--type`, `--domain`, `--occurred-at`, `--source`, `--evidence`, `--project`, `--person`, `--tags`, and `--capture-raw`.

If `record` returns `needs_more_detail`, ask for time, object, result, or evidence. Use `--capture-raw` only when the user explicitly wants to keep the raw fragment.

When `record` succeeds, inspect `projectionRefresh` together with `fact`, `ruleProjection`, and `assetPrecipitation` to see whether passport/manual/exchange projections refreshed or stayed as raw candidates.

## Common Commands

- Register: `lifeos register --name "Name" --password "password"`
- Login: `lifeos login --name "Name" --password "password"`
- Configure: `lifeos configure --base-url "https://example.com/lifeos" --name "Name"`
- Record durable context: `lifeos record --text "..."`
- Save daily plan: `lifeos plan save --input-json '{...}'`
- Confirm daily plan: `lifeos plan confirm`
- Complete planned action: `lifeos action done --input-json '{...}'` writes a projected action fact
- Read snapshot: `lifeos snapshot`
- Read profile: `lifeos profile get`
- Read scores: `lifeos score get`
- Read assets: `lifeos asset list`

Use `fact add`, `profile capture`, and `asset add` only for explicit advanced writes or compatibility. They are not the default recording path.

## Profile Initialization

Before profile/scoring-dependent workflows, run:

```bash
lifeos profile get
```

If uninitialized, collect the 10 initialization answers naturally, 1-3 questions at a time, then run `lifeos profile init --input-json '{...}'`.

## Rules

- Treat CLI output as JSON; claim success only when `"ok": true`.
- Do not fabricate facts or initialization answers.
- Keep facts objective and based on user-provided information.
- Ask before recording sensitive personal information.
- Do not expose tokens, passwords, or local config contents.
- Do not write to LifeOS when the user only asks for advice, a draft, or a hypothetical plan.
